The paper proposes a strategy for ridesharing with integrated transit transfers, which involves designing and testing online solution algorithms for vehicle dispatch and idle vehicle relocation. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) for the algorithm design, as well as systems and control (cs.SY) for the overall strategy. Additionally, the paper mentions queueing theory and optimization, which are relevant to computer engineering (cs.CE) and information theory (cs.IT).
